      q: 'When should my child have their first dental visit?',
      a: 'The American Academy of Pediatric Dentistry recommends a first dental visit by age 1, or within 6 months after the first tooth appears. Early visits let us monitor development, apply preventive treatments, and help parents establish good home care routines.',
    },
    {
      q: 'How do you handle anxious or fearful kids?',
